The Flash (The stolen Idea)
They call him the Scarlet Speedster, first appearing in Flash Comics issue one in January 1940. He was said to be created by Gardner Fox and Harry Lampert, but the story behind his creation runs deeper than most fans know.

Before The Flash ever raced across pages, earlier pulp stories featured heroes who could move faster than the eye could see. Characters like Mercury, the Roman god of speed, and comic figures from the 1930s shared strikingly similar traits. Some say The Flash was not a new idea but a perfected copy.

Years later, artist Carmine Infantino filed lawsuits against DC Comics, claiming that he created more than just the suit. He said he designed Wally West, Iris West, Captain Cold, and other major parts of the universe that made The Flash legendary. His credit was never fully restored, and the case faded into silence.

Maybe the fastest man alive wasnât born from a spark of lightning, but from ideas borrowed and repainted.
Some legends are written.
Others are taken.

Usher, born Usher Raymond IV on October 14, 1978, is an American R&B singer, songwriter, and dancer renowned for his smooth vocals, impressive dance moves, and chart-topping hits. Rising to fame in the late '90s with albums like My Way and 8701, Usher established himself as a major force in R&B. His 2004 album, Confessions, is one of the best-selling R&B albums of all time, featuring hits like "Yeah!" and "Burn," and is often credited with defining the sound of modern R&B.

Throughout his career, Usher has collaborated with several major artists, including Alicia Keys, with whom he recorded the iconic duet "My Boo." Their chemistry in the song resonated with fans, and it became an anthem of the 2000s, showcasing both of their vocal talents and romantic storytelling. This collaboration highlighted Usher's ability to create timeless music and cemented both artists as R&B icons.

Usher continues to make music, perform, and inspire new artists. Known for his captivating performances and genre-defining hits, he remains an influential figure in R&B. With eight Grammy Awards and numerous chart-toppers, his impact on music is undeniable, and his work with artists like Alicia Keys adds to his legacy as one of the greatest R&B artists of his generation.

- **Engine Options:** The Grand i10 typically offers a range of engine options, including petrol and diesel variants. The engines are designed to deliver a balance of performance and fuel efficiency.
